solution: ```class Solution {
    public int countCharacters(String[] words, String chars) {
        int[] freq = new int[26];
        for (char c : chars.toCharArray()) freq[c - 'a']++;
        int sum = 0;
        for (String w : words) {
            int[] need = new int[26];
            boolean ok = true;
            for (char c : w.toCharArray()) {
                int idx = c - 'a';
                need[idx]++;
                if (need[idx] > freq[idx]) {
                    ok = false;
                    break;
                }
            }
            if (ok) sum += w.length();
        }
        return sum;
    }
}```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(N * L) where N = words.length and L = average word length
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Count frequency of each character in chars once. For each word, count its characters and check against the global frequency array; if all counts are ≤ the global counts, add the word’s length to the result. Uses fixed-size arrays for O(1) space.

